  <title>Electric Energy and Potential</title>
	<introduction>
    <p> In this chapter you will learn about electric energy and electric potential</p>
	
	</introduction>
		
    <objectives>
      
      <introduction><p>After successful completion of this chapter, you will be able to:</p></introduction>
		<ol>
			<li><p>Determine the electric potential energy in a system of charged objects.</p></li>
			<li><p>Distinguish between the electric potential energy stored in a system and the electric potential due to a charge configuration.</p></li>
			<li><p>Determine the electric potential due to a system of charged objects.</p></li>
			<li><p>Use an energy approach to analyze electrostatics systems.</p></li>
		</ol>
	</objectives>

